      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve. The drivetrain is anchored by a 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, offering precise gear synchronization and mechanical feedback. This example has been maintained with a focus on preventative engineering, including a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal replacement. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that provides exceptional lateral stability and communicative hydraulic steering. While the exterior shows minor patina consistent with high-speed touring, the powertrain remains robust with no signs of bore scoring or oil aeration. It is a mechanically sound specimen primed for spirited canyon carving.",
